Package: epsontmt20iv
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, cups, cups-filters, ghostscript
Description: CUPS thermal driver for the Epson TM-T20IV (ePOS over HTTPS)
 Prints 80 mm thermal tickets to an Epson TM-T20IV. This printer only accepts
 Epson's ePOS-Print protocol over HTTPS - its raw port 9100 is non-functional -
 so the stock Epson, gutenprint and escpr CUPS drivers cannot drive it over the
 network.
 .
 This package provides a CUPS raster filter (rastertotmt20iv) that renders each
 page to a 1-bit image, an "epos" CUPS backend that POSTs it to the printer, and
 a PPD for the 80 mm roll (576 dots at 203 dpi).
 .
 Installing the package does not create a print queue, because the queue needs
 the printer's IP address. See /usr/share/doc/epsontmt20iv/README.Debian for the
 single lpadmin command that sets it up.
